It may be that the mechanism of action for programming people is to determine whether a feeling is positive or negative.
After something intense happens, adrenaline passes through the body, the adrenaline is a signal used to condition the intense thing that happened with your feeling at that moment. The decision whether it is good or bad, belongs only to a person through culture.
This does not contradict the fact that sometimes there are things that release other substances, like serotonin or dopamine that have a clear positive effect.